to the editor david brooks makes a very good point about the personal nature of many political criticisms column sept 30 but one has only to look at the policies of the current administration to find the reasons for the current disagreements and complaints the arguments proceed not from the personal failings of the president but from an ideology that has led to policies that many find to be abhorrent and citizen unfriendly what goes on in the white house today affects us all now and for years to come luisa francoeur westport conn sept 30 2003

